reviews.text: If you fancy a quiet place to drink around Taipo with a traditional English pub feel then look no further.   No cigarette stink with telly shows live footy and rugby matches,  and decent pub food too.
Service was poor, staff continually had to reconfirm our order. Manager yelling at staff. Food is decent but untrained staff really ruins it.
A simple pub. Warm, friendly, good service.
Awesome bar. Friendly staff. Excellent variety of drinks. Excellent food. Fair price. Excellent vibe. Easily one of if not the best bar in Tai Po.
Excellent bar to chill in Tai Po. Fair price around $65 for a pint during happy hour. Wings and burgers are great you shouldn't miss out.
